.TH "XUT" "1" "2025-08-02"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
\fBxut\fR - install software for void-linux using unofficial \fBx\fRtra \fBu\fRser \fBt\fRemplates.\&
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBxut\fR [-lshu] [-b \fIpackages1,package2,.\&.\&.\&\fR | -i \fIpackages1,package2,.\&.\&.\&\fR] [-x <xbps-src command>] [-q <query>]
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The xut utility used unofficial user-provided templates for xbps-src in git repos to provide
additional software for a void-linux installation.\& 
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-s\fR	
.RS 4
Sync the configured repositories.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-l\fR
.RS 4
Enable logging to a file.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-h\fR
.RS 4
Display usage information.\&
.PP
.PP
.RE
\fB-b <package1,package2>\fR
.RS 4
Build a list of (comma-seperated) packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-i <package1,package2>\fR
.RS 4
Build and install a list of (comma-seperated) packages.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-x\fR 
.RS 4
Executed xbps-src commands.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-q\fR <query>
.RS 4
Search for <query> in available templates.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-u\fR
.RS 4
Update packages.\&
.PP
.PP
.RE
.SS Notes for cli arguments
.RS 4
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
If \fB-x\fR is used, \fB-b\fR and \fB-p\fR will be ignored.\&
.IP \(bu 4
\fB-b\fR and \fB-i\fR cannot be used in the same command.\&
.IP \(bu 4
\fB-l\fR and \fB-s\fR are meant to be used with the other arguments (\fB-x,\fR, \fB-b\fR and \fB-i\fR).\&
.IP \(bu 4
\fB-l\fR enables "debug" messages in the output, which becomes more verbose.\&
.PD
.PP
.RE
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
.RS 4
\fBxut\fR has very limited configuration.\&
By default it clones and syncs the void-packages repository and the abyss-packages from codeberg
and uses the templates of the second one to build and install additional packages.\&
It can be used without any additional configuration, but it can be configured by a \fI.\&xutconf\fR file.\&
Please see the sample configuration in \fI/usr/share/doc/xutconf.\&sample\fR for more.\&
By default, \fBxut\fR uses the \fI$HOME/.\&xut\fR directory as a working directory.\& It clones and syns repos there, keeps logs
if the user enables that with the \fB-l\fR arguments in the log/ subdirectory.\&
.PP
.PP
.RE
